-- Canada Ivey Purchasing Index Reaches Highest in 14 Months
-- B y   A n d r e w   M a y e d a
-- 2013-06-06T14:43:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-06/canada-ivey-purchasing-index-reaches-highest-in-14-months.html
 Canada’s Ivey purchasing managers’
 index  rose to the highest in 14 months in May, surpassing the
most optimistic of economists’ expectations.  The index rose to 63.1 on a seasonally adjusted basis from
a reading of 52.2 in April, according to a statement on the
website of Western University’s business school. Readings of
more than 50 indicate purchasing by governments and companies
advanced. A  survey  of 12 economists by Bloomberg News had a
median estimate of 56.0.  Canada’s economy expanded at the fastest pace since 2011 in
the first three months of the year, as oil producers ramped up
shipments to the U.S, Statistics Canada reported May 31.  Among related indexes, the employment figure fell to 51.4
from 55.1, while the inventories index rose to 58.3 from 52.7.
The supplier delivery measure increased to 49.8 from 49.5, and
the price index rose to 63.2 from 58.7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
